                <h4 class="page-row-title fw-700 text-charcoal">Simple and intuitive features</h4>

                <p class="body-2 text-manatee">
                    Features are what drive modern web applications, and whilst a large number of usable features is great, we believe that a moderate number 
                    of really useful features is even more important. We’ve decided to narrow our current features to three simple yet intuitive features that 
                    our users can take full advantage from. Like the ability to search for what you need using keywords like #baker or #ice-cream, being able 
                    to filter your search results down to a more digestible number of results, and being able to open your choice in Google Maps to find where you need to go.
                </p>

                <h6 class="page-row-subtitle fw-600 text-charcoal m-t-50 m-b-20">Search using specific keywords</h6>

                <p class="body-2 text-manatee">
                    We decided to incorporate keyword based searching capabilities as it streamlines the search process to allow users to get to their results 
                    quicker.  If you’d like to narrow down the search results by a specific category, or in this instance, keyword, you can do just that in order 
                    to avoid the added fluff and overwhelming decision process present in the unknown search of what you’re looking for. Keyword based search also 
                    allows us to limit the number of overwhelming searching functionality as our main goal is to make this part of the process easier for users.
                </p>

                <h6 class="page-row-subtitle fw-600 text-charcoal m-t-50 m-b-20">Filter your results to narrow your search</h6>

                <p class="body-2 text-manatee">
                    You can filter your search results by what’s most relevant to you in a number of categories. You can filter your search results by most relevant, 
                    most popular, etc., in order to get to good choices quicker. Our filter processor is always improving and will continue to become more expansive 
                    in offering you more and more filtering choices that will help you narrow the search down even further. For now, we’ve developed a simple filter 
                    system that works in tandem with our database collection that will get you up and running in no time.
                </p>

                <h6 class="page-row-subtitle fw-600 text-charcoal m-t-50 m-b-20">Open a pick on Google Maps</h6>

                <p class="body-2 text-manatee">
                    Google Maps is one of the largest and most robust maps solution available today. Offering real-time updates, satellite and geographical views, 
                    and most importantly, navigation features that can be tailored to your needs. We believe that finding the restaurant to eat from is just half the 
                    experience, being able to see where it is and how to get there is the other half. Integrating Google Maps with findDining helps us bridge that 
                    gap and allow our users to take that next step in visiting and actually trying out their food spots.
                </p>
